One person has been confirmed dead after a heavy-duty vehicle rammed into a motorcycle on Thursday night at Nnewi in Anambra State. The Federal Road Safety Corps Sector Commander in the state, Mr Andrew Kumapayi, confirmed the accident to newsmen in Awka on Friday. Kumapayi said the accident occurred along Ozubulu road, Awka. “It was gathered that a blue and white Honda motorcycle, without a registration number, was hit by a Mercedes-Benz 911 tipper with registration number XH712PHC. “One ( the motorcyclist) out of the three male adults involved in the crash lost his life,’’ he said. He also said the body of the accident victim has been deposited at St. Felix Okolo Hospital at Nnewi, NAN reports.